HEADWORD: disa
<hw>disa</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any orchid of the genus
<gen>Disa</gen>, a genus of beautiful orchids with dark green leaves and
usually hooded flowers; -- they are much prized as emblematic flowers in
their native regions.</def>⟦br⟧
